    <h2 class="section-title">Experienced, Compassionate Psychiatric Care</h2>
    <p>Lisa Anderson earned her Bachelor's degree in Nursing from Indiana University of Pennsylvania, followed by a Master's in Nursing Administration from LaRoche College in Pittsburgh, PA. She then completed an additional Master's program earning her license as a Psychiatric Mental Health Nurse Practitioner (PMHNP) at Regis College in Weston, MA.</p>
    <p>With over 30 years of extensive nursing experience — including a decade in public health school nursing — Lisa brings a uniquely broad perspective to psychiatric care. Her background spans inpatient psychiatric hospitals, adolescent and adult inpatient facilities, and community healthcare settings.</p>
    <p>Her practice prioritizes alleviating symptoms, strengthening coping mechanisms, and guiding individuals toward stability and fulfillment.</p>
